other_tests.findings: Mucosal enhancement and enlargement of the appendix which is enlarged, measuring 7-8 mm. No pleural effusion, nodule, or opacity is present at the lung bases. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and ureters are within normal limits. A nonenhancing 1 cm simple cyst is noted in the upper pole of the right kidney. Diverticulosis of the large bowel without evidence of diverticulitis. No free air or fluid is seen in the peritoneal cavity. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy is identified. Diverticulosis of the sigmoid colon is noted without evidence of diverticulitis. Small bilateral hydroceles are identified.
